{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775845049636,"sessionID":"ses_287634581ffeL0pRpQsfF3cZ8a","part":{"id":"prt_d789d01de001Td5rtD7f0VuPgA","messageID":"msg_d789cf87a001GKyn1w58hvbd6L","sessionID":"ses_287634581ffeL0pRpQsfF3cZ8a","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_9ccafa255cb648fe9265b0f4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-007/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-007/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-007 — K8s Reconciler 控制器\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the Kubernetes Reconciler controller in `pkg/workloadmanager`. The Reconciler is responsible for watching and reconciling Sandbox custom resources with actual Kubernetes resources (Pods, Services, ConfigMaps), ensuring the desired state matches the actual cluster state.\n6: \n7: ## Base Specifications\n8: \n9: - **AR**: AR-007\n10: - **Module**: `pkg/workloadmanager`\n11: - **Language**: Go\n12: - **Size**: L\n13: - **Depends On**: AR-005 (Sandbox 创建处理器), AR-006 (Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理)\n14: \n15: ---\n16: \n17: ## Scenario: Reconciler Core Loop\n18: \n19: ### AR-007-001: Reconciler Startup\n20: \n21: - **GIVEN** the workloadmanager service starting\n22: - **WHEN** the Reconciler is initialized\n23: - **THEN** the Reconciler SHALL register a Controller for Sandbox resources\n24: - **AND** SHALL start informers for Sandbox, Pod, Service, ConfigMap resources\n25: - **AND** SHALL start the reconciliation loop with a worker pool\n26: - **AND** SHALL log startup status and configuration\n27: \n28: ### AR-007-002: Reconcile Create Event\n29: \n30: - **GIVEN** a new Sandbox CR is created in the cluster\n31: - **WHEN** the Reconciler receives a Create event\n32: - **THEN** the Reconciler SHALL fetch the Sandbox object\n33: - **AND** SHALL validate the Sandbox spec\n34: - **AND** SHALL create the corresponding Pod resource\n35: - **AND** SHALL create associated Services (if needed)\n36: - **AND** SHALL create associated ConfigMaps (if needed)\n37: - **AND** SHALL update Sandbox status to Running\n38: - **AND** SHALL set ownerReference for all created resources\n39: \n40: ### AR-007-003: Reconcile Update Event\n41: \n42: - **GIVEN** an existing Sandbox with modifications to spec\n43: - **WHEN** the Reconciler receives an Update event\n44: - **THEN** the Reconciler SHALL detect changed fields\n45: - **AND** SHALL update the Pod with new specifications (image, env, resources)\n46: - **AND** SHALL update Services if needed\n47: - **AND** SHALL update ConfigMaps if needed\n48: - **AND** SHALL log all reconciliation actions\n49: \n50: ### AR-007-004: Reconcile Delete Event\n51: \n52: - **GIVEN** a Sandbox CR is deleted\n53: - **WHEN** the Reconciler receives a Delete event\n54: - **THEN** the Reconciler SHALL perform final cleanup\n55: - **AND** SHALL ensure all owned resources are deleted\n56: - **AND** SHALL handle cascade deletion via ownerReferences\n57: \n58: ### AR-007-005: Periodic Reconciliation\n59: \n60: - **GIVEN** a running Reconciler\n61: - **WHEN** the periodic sync interval elapses (default 30 seconds)\n62: - **THEN** the Reconciler SHALL scan all Sandboxes\n63: - **AND** SHALL verify actual cluster state matches desired state\n64: - **AND** SHALL repair any drift detected\n65: - **AND** SHALL update Sandbox status with current state\n66: \n67: ---\n68: \n69: ## Scenario: Error Handling & Retry\n70: \n71: ### AR-007-010: Retry on Transient Errors\n72: \n73: - **GIVEN** a reconciliation fails due to transient error (API server temporarily unavailable)\n74: - **THEN** the Reconciler SHALL retry with exponential backoff\n75: - **AND** SHALL retry up to 5 times with increasing delays (1s, 2s, 4s, 8s, 16s)\n76: - **AND** SHALL log each retry attempt\n77: - **AND** SHALL update Sandbox status to reflect reconciliation failure after max retries\n78: \n79: ### AR-007-011: Permanent Error Handling\n80: \n81: - **GIVEN** a reconciliation fails due to permanent error (invalid spec, insufficient resources)\n82: - **THEN** the Reconciler SHALL NOT retry\n83: - **AND** SHALL set Sandbox status to Failed\n84: - **AND** SHALL add a condition with error details\n85: - **AND** SHALL emit a Kubernetes Event for the failure\n86: \n87: ### AR-007-012: Conflict Handling\n88: \n89: - **GIVEN** a reconciliation detects resource version conflict\n90: - **THEN** the Reconciler SHALL fetch the latest version\n91: - **AND** SHALL re-apply the desired state\n92: - **AND** SHALL log the conflict resolution\n93: \n94: ---\n95: \n96: ## Scenario: Resource Synchronization\n97: \n98: ### AR-007-020: Pod Status Sync\n99: \n100: - **GIVEN** a Sandbox with a managed Pod\n101: - **WHEN** the Pod status changes (Pending, Running, Succeeded, Failed, Unknown)\n102: - **THEN** the Reconciler SHALL sync Pod status to Sandbox status\n103: - **AND** SHALL update Sandbox conditions (PodReady, ContainersReady)\n104: - **AND** SHALL record Pod restart count and container states\n105: \n106: ### AR-007-021: Service Discovery Sync\n107: \n108: - **GIVEN** a Sandbox with managed Services\n109: - **WHEN** Service endpoints change\n110: - **THEN** the Reconciler SHALL update Sandbox status with endpoint info\n111: - **AND** SHALL track ready replicas\n112: \n113: ### AR-007-022: Orphan Resource Detection\n114: \n115: - **GIVEN** a Pod/Service/ConfigMap with ownerReference to a non-existent Sandbox\n116: - **THEN** the Reconciler SHALL log a warning\n117: - **AND** SHALL consider implementing automatic cleanup for orphaned resources\n118: \n119: ---\n120: \n121: ## Scenario: Scaling & Performance\n122: \n123: ### AR-007-030: Parallel Reconciliation\n124: \n125: - **GIVEN** multiple Sandbox resources needing reconciliation\n126: - **WHEN** the worker pool has multiple workers\n127: - **THEN** the Reconciler SHALL process multiple Sandboxes in parallel\n128: - **AND** SHALL limit concurrent reconciles per namespace (default: 10)\n129: - **AND** SHALL use workqueue for rate limiting\n130: \n131: ### AR-007-031: Reconcile Rate Limiting\n132: \n133: - **GIVEN** high reconciliation frequency\n134: - **WHEN** the queue depth exceeds threshold\n135: - **THEN** the Reconciler SHALL implement rate limiting\n136: - **AND** SHALL use bucket4j or similar for rate limiting\n137: - **AND** SHALL prioritize critical operations (delete > update > create)\n138: \n139: ### AR-007-032: Efficient Informers\n140: \n141: - **GIVEN** large number of Sandbox resources\n142: - **WHEN** the Reconciler starts\n143: - **THEN** the Reconciler SHALL use indexed informers\n144: - **AND** SHALL filter by namespace when possible\n145: - **AND** SHALL use label selectors to reduce unnecessary reconciles\n146: \n147: ---\n148: \n149: ## Scenario: Status & Conditions\n150: \n151: ### AR-007-040: Status Conditions\n152: \n153: - **GIVEN** a Sandbox resource\n154: - **THEN** the Reconciler SHALL maintain status.conditions:\n155:   - **PodScheduled**: boolean indicating if Pod is scheduled\n156:   - **ContainersReady**: boolean indicating if all containers are ready\n157:   - **Initialized**: boolean indicating if init containers completed\n158:   - **Reconciled**: boolean indicating if reconciliation succeeded\n159:   - **Failed**: boolean with reason if reconciliation failed\n160: \n161: ### AR-007-041: Status Phase\n162: \n163: - **GIVEN** a Sandbox resource\n164: - **THEN** the Reconciler SHALL set status.phase:\n165:   - **Pending**: Sandbox created, reconciliation in progress\n166:   - **Running**: Pod is running and ready\n167:   - **Succeeded**: Pod completed successfully\n168:   - **Failed**: Pod failed or reconciliation failed\n169:   - **Unknown**: Unable to determine state\n170: \n171: ### AR-007-042: Status Metrics\n172: \n173: - **GIVEN** a running Reconciler\n174: - **THEN** the Reconciler SHALL expose Prometheus metrics:\n175:   - `sandbox_reconcile_total{result=\"success|failure\"}`\n176:   - `sandbox_reconcile_duration_seconds`\n177:   - `sandbox_reconcile_retries_total`\n178:   - `sandbox_workqueue_depth`\n179: \n180: ---\n181: \n182: ## Scenario: Testing & Observability\n183: \n184: ### AR-007-050: Reconcile Logging\n185: \n186: - **GIVEN** reconciliation operations\n187: - **THEN** the Reconciler SHALL log:\n188:   - Reconciliation trigger (create/update/periodic/delete)\n189:   - Sandbox identifier (name, namespace, UID)\n190:   - Actions taken (created/updated/deleted resources)\n191:   - Errors encountered\n192:   - Duration of reconciliation\n193: \n194: ### AR-007-051: Structured Error Messages\n195: \n196: - **GIVEN** reconciliation errors\n197: - **THEN** the Reconciler SHALL provide structured error info:\n198:   - Error code\n199:   - Resource that caused the error\n200:   - Suggested action for resolution\n201:   - Relevant CRD fields\n202: \n203: ### AR-007-052: Health Checks\n204: \n205: - **GIVEN** a running workloadmanager service\n206: - **WHEN** health check endpoint is called\n207: - **THEN** the Reconciler SHALL report:\n208:   - Informer sync status (synced/not synced)\n209:   - Workqueue depth\n210:   - Last reconciliation timestamp\n211: \n212: ---\n213: \n214: ## References\n215: \n216: - Delta Spec: `changes/AR-007/delta-spec.md`\n217: - Related AR: AR-005 (Sandbox 创建处理器), AR-006 (Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理)\n218: - Kubernetes Controller Pattern: https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/architecture/controller/\n219: - Controller Runtime: https://book.kubebuilder.io/cronjob-tutorial/controller-overview.html\n220: - Sandbox CRD: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/`\n\n(End of file - total 220 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-007 — K8s Reconciler 控制器\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the Kubernetes Reconciler controller in `pkg/workloadmanager`. The Reconciler is responsible for watching and reconciling Sandbox custom resources with actual Kubernetes resources (Pods, Services, ConfigMaps), ensuring the desired state matches the actual cluster state.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-007\n- **Module**: `pkg/workloadmanager`\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: L\n- **Depends On**: AR-005 (Sandbox 创建处理器), AR-006 (Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理)\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: Reconciler Core Loop\n\n### AR-007-001: Reconciler Startup\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-007/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775845049625,"end":1775845049633}}}}
